<br>
You won't get paid much... $10 an hour is pretty standard.  Choose your job based on 2 factors:<br>
1) the variety of Japanese you'll be required to speak and listen to  (a repetitive narrator's job would suck, but a hotel info/help-desk or tour agent's in-hotel desk would be excellent).<br>
and<br>
2) the amount of quality study-time you can do on the job.  (Again, hotel info-desk or tour agent's in-hotel desk would be IDEAL.  You can browse through pamphlets, label everything in sight, wander through your dictionary... and you're sitting all day in an air-conditioned room, as opposed to standing in an airport or bouncing around in a tour-bus or standing in a clothing store waiting for customers to arrive.)<br>
<br>
Of course, these jobs will hire you based on YOUR proficiency, so you may have to hunt around before you find a company that'll let you start stoooopid and train-up while on the job.<br>
<br>
Hawaii (and Guam) are crappy job markets right now.  Hawaii has plenty of jobs, but all low-paying.  Guam has the same low-paying jobs, but fewer of them, and a much smaller talent-pool of Japanese speakers.<br>
<br>
You're quarter-this, quarter-that, born in Hawaii ?  You LUCKY  DOG !!!!  I'm pure German-looking, and Mainlander Haole.  In Hawaii, I was constantly wishing I had genes and a birthplace like yours.  Every place I went, people said &quot;Look... here comes Haole-Boy.  White as a ghost, long pants, no aloha shirt, even though it's Friday.  Toooooouuuuurrrriiiiiiisssssttttt !~<br>
Betcha he has socks on, between his feet an' his rubbah slippahs.&quot;<br>
==========<br>
<br>
Once you get to Japan, you CAN work under-the-table teaching English.  There's lots of competition, though, and it takes about a year to get a full-time schedule of students.  Oh, and if another private teacher gets jealous of you, he can always call the cops on you.  Anddddd... students will constantly be trying to get you to lower your prices, do free stuff, do language exchanges... anything so they get free English practice.  It's kinda tiring.<br>
<br>
If I were you, I'd solve the housing problem by looking for a homestay situation until you've got enough classes going to pay for your own pad....and know the city well enough to find a decent place to live.  You can probably find a family willing to take you in, based on their chance to chat you up in English.  Kinda like instant celebrity status, isn't it ?  They might ask you to teach their kids a bit.  You can use that as a starting point, asking them to recruit paying kids from the nieghborhood, to join the classes.  The same for the host-family adults.<br>
<br>
Do you look European-ish, or Asian-ish ?  In Hawaii, looking asian will help your job prospects, because tourists will assume that you can speak and relate to them in their language and culture, so they'll relax a bit.  (This is totally unfair, of course, but...those're the facts, not the world we wish for.)  On the other hand, if you look European but your Japanese is totally hot, you'll get alot of amused customers who'll tip you heavily and want their photo taken with you.  <br>
<br>
In Japan, on the other hand, LOOKING Asian isn't gonna help you much at English lessons.  In fact, it hurts in alotta ways.  Many schools and students won't trust your ability as an English speaker, if you look Asian.  The feeling is sort of like if you went into a Chinese restaurant, and the chef was some German/Italian guy.  <br>
<br>
Your career-path-- Manga cartooning-- is a tough one in Japan.  You're setting yourself up to compete with Japanese artists in a Japanese office, at Japanese regular-guy salaries...which stink.  If I were you, I'd look for a career in Japan AT a manga-office, but doing an English-writing job there.  Think of all the software and cartoons that can be translated into English and sold around the world... !!!  You can't read Japanese well enough, of course, but lots of Japanese offices will set you loose in the office to help put the final touches on translations that have been started by Japanese guys learning English.<br>
<br>
Before you get to Japan, see if you can take a TESOL (teaching English as a foreign language) course, 1 month long.  That'll help with your English-teaching job prospects.<br>
<br>
Also, take a Japanese Language Proficiency Test (writing, reading, and listening skills).  You won't be anywhere near the level-2 that you'd need to function perfectly in a Japanese-only office, but it'll start your credentials rolling... and Japanese employers LIVE for credentials.  Knowing the subject means squat in japan... certificates PROVING you know the subject mean EVERYTHING.  The JLPT will get the ball rolling for you. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm5.showPrevMessage?topicID=1227.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm5.showNextMessage?topicID=1227.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1227.topic&index=13><img src=http://www.polykarbon.com/bbsimage/addreply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm5.emailToFriend?topicID=1227.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm5.threadControl?topicID=1227.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm5.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=1227.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/subscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to receive email notification of replies"> Click to receive email notification of replies</a> <br>  <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm5.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=1227.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/unsubscribe.gif width=20 height=20 bor